        <fileDesc>
            <titleStmt>
                <title>Thomas Pennant to Daines Barrington, presenting Shaw's 'Ecclesiastical
                    antiquities of Murray'</title>
            </titleStmt>
            <publicationStmt>
                <publisher/>
            </publicationStmt>
            <sourceDesc>
                <msDesc>
                    <msIdentifier>
                        <settlement>London</settlement>
                        <repository>Society of Antiquaries of London</repository>
                        <idno>SAL/MS/32</idno>
                    </msIdentifier>
                    <msContents>
                        <p>
                            <locus>5-6</locus>
                        </p>
                    </msContents>
                    <additional>
                        <p>This letter is followed in the binding by 21 single-sided folios in
                            another hand, detailing the establishment of religious orders and
                            buildings in Scotland and titled by Pennant: 'of the Ecclesiastical
                            antiquities of Murray.' The manuscript may be a copy of part of the work
                            that would later be published as Lachlan Shaw's <bibl type="editorial">
                                <title ref="bi0081">
                                    <hi rend="italic">History of the Province of
                                        Moray</hi>
                                </title> (London: 1775)</bibl>, which Pennant had
                            acquired for use in compiling his <bibl type="editorial">
                                <title ref="bi0004">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Tour in Scotland
                                    1769</hi>
                                </title>: see 3rd edn. (Warrington: 1769), Appendix
                                II., <biblScope unit="page">pp.287-312</biblScope>
                            </bibl>.</p>
                    </additional>
                </msDesc>
            </sourceDesc>
        </fileDesc>
