    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>To The Hon<hi rend="superscript">ble</hi>
                    <persName ref="pe0598">Daines Barrington</persName>
                    <dateline>march 4.<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1773</dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am honored by the report you made of the acceptance of my poor services from
                    The Society of antiquaries. I am mortified much at the delay of correspondents
                    from whom I expected materials for forming an account of the sacred antiquities
                    of <placeName ref="pl0708">the <hi rend="underline">Hebrides:</hi>
                    </placeName>
                    <hi rend="underline">en attendant</hi>, let me beg the favor of you to introduce
                    the following account of the antiquities of <hi rend="underline">
                        <placeName ref="pl0145">Elgin</placeName>
                    </hi> &amp; other places in the <placeName ref="pl1141">Shire of <hi rend="underline">Murray</hi>
                    </placeName> composed
                    by <persName ref="pe0265">the revd M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        <hi rend="underline">Shaw</hi>
                    </persName> The venerable minister of
                        <placeName ref="pl0145">its Capital</placeName>, aged <sic>ninty</sic>.</p>
                <p>I am with True regard, Dear Sir,</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Your obliged &amp; faithfull humble Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Thomas Pennant</persName>.</signed>
                </closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p>This is attended by two drawings one <rs type="art" ref="ar0118">a general
                            view</rs> of <placeName ref="pe0232">
                            <hi rend="underline">Elgin</hi>
                        </placeName> after <persName ref="pe0330                             ">Sandby</persName>; the other
                            <rs type="art" ref="ar0119">a view of the Chapter house</rs> after the
                        ingenious <persName ref="pe0599">
                            <hi rend="underline">Bernard</hi>
                            <hi rend="underline">Gilpin</hi> esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> of <hi rend="underline">Carlisle</hi>.</persName>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
